Subject: Re: [T2] How hot is HOT?

PV=nRT is the equation of state for an ideal gas.  Liquids have a totally
different equation of state.  The primary controlling phenomenon is that the
viscosity of liquids decreases with increasing temperature.

Higher temperature = lower viscosity = lower oil pressure.

